<item>
            <title>[SYNAPSE-269] Fix the dual channel invocation of synapse as a client</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-269</link>
                <project id="12310201" key="SYNAPSE">Synapse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Synapse should properly support the dual channel invocation when executing as a client (i.e. when synapse invokes an actual service to get the response for a mediated request).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To support this the configuration has to specify this to the engine which can be done by using the &amp;lt;enableAddressing separateListener=&quot;true&quot;/&amp;gt; tag and need to fix the functionality.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>All envs</environment>
